   <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.03702.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                  <date when="1887-03-11">Peoria, Ill. Mar. 11, '87</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Mr. Whitman:</salute>
            </opener>
            <p> The evening's readings, skeletonized in the enclosed slip, were given by an ardent
                lover of both of us&#8212;my husband. He was called away from home immediately
                after the occasion described, and asked me to forward a review of the evening to
                you&#8212;the occasion of it, and I take pleasure in complying with his request both
                for his sake and yours.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Sincerely your friend&#8212;in the spirit,</salute>
                <signed>Mrs. Wm Hawley Smith</signed>
            </closer>  
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.03702.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
